  "title": "Curtain & Interior Furnishing Installer (Operator)",
  "description": "<p>Roles &amp; Responsibilities:</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are looking for a reliable and motivated individuals to join our installation team.</p>\n<p>you are physically fit, responsible, eager to learn, and enjoy working in a hands-on environment, we’d love to hear from you!</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Key Responsibilities:</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Assist in the installation of curtains, blinds, zipblinds, wallpapers, and vinyl flooring.</p>\n<p>Provide on-site technical support and basic troubleshooting for clients.</p>\n<p>Prepare, pack, and organize installation tools, equipment, and materials.</p>\n<p>Maintain cleanliness and safety at work sites during and after installations.</p>\n<p>Work closely with the team to ensure timely and quality completion of jobs.</p>\n<p>Operate company vehicles to transport materials and team members (Good to have valid Class 3 driving license but not compulsory).</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Preferred Skills &amp; Requirements:</p>\n<p>Prior experience in curtain, blinds, wallpaper, or vinyl installation is an advantage but not mandatory.</p>\n<p>Good to have a valid Class 3 driver’s license but not compulsory</p>\n<p>Physically able to handle heavy lifting and work on ladders or scaffolding if needed.</p>\n<p>Good communication skills and a team-oriented attitude.</p>\n<p>Willingness to learn new skills and take on various installation-related tasks.</p>",
